  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://Rook-io.slack.com).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nWhen a cluster orchestration is started, the version of the ceph image is determined by launching the image and getting the major version name from the output of `ceph --version`. When the crd is later updated with the intention of upgrading, the major version is correctly detected, but then is not updated in memory.\r\n\r\nFor example, if updating the crd to nautilus from mimic, the messages are seen in the operator log:\r\n```\r\n2018-12-08 04:36:45.227659 I | op-cluster: the ceph version changed. detecting the new image version...\r\n2018-12-08 04:36:45.241504 I | op-k8sutil: waiting for job rook-ceph-detect-version to complete...\r\n2018-12-08 04:36:50.409846 I | op-cluster: detected ceph version nautilus for image ceph/daemon-base:master\r\n2018-12-08 04:36:50.409882 W | op-cluster: overriding ceph version to mimic specified in the CRD\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe last message is incorrect. It should apply \"nautilus\" as detected, instead of retaining \"mimic\".\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nThe major version should always be accurate in order to perform the orchestration steps.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n* Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n* Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod):\r\n* Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n* Kubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift):\r\n* Storage backend status (e.g. for Ceph use `ceph health` in the [Rook Ceph toolbox](https://rook.io/docs/Rook/master/toolbox.html)):\r\n",
